casebody.data:
Amadeo T. YBARRA, Appellant, v. BROTHERHOOD RAILWAY CARMEN OF AMERICA, Appellee. No. 21519. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit Feb. 15, 1965. J. Marvin Ericson, Corpus Christi, Tex., for appellant. Donald W. Fisher, Toledo, Ohio, Homer L. Deakins, Jr., Houston, Tex., Fulbright, Crooker, Freeman, Bates & Jaworski, Houston, Tex., Mulholland, Hickey & Lyman, Toledo, Ohio, of counsel, for ap-pellee.

Before BROWN and BELL, Circuit Judges, and HUNTER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM:

The judgment of the district court will be Affirmed on the opinion of Judge Garza, 227 F.Supp. 171.
